---
import PageLayout from "~/layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import { getPageTitle, SITE_NAME } from "~/lib/config";

const metadata = {
  title: getPageTitle("Terms of Service"),
  description: "Terms of Service for " + SITE_NAME,
  noindex: true,
};
---

<PageLayout metadata={metadata}>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Last updated: {
            new Date().toLocaleDateString("en-US", {
              year: "numeric",
              month: "long",
              day: "numeric",
            })
          }
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">
          1. Agreement to Terms
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          By accessing or using our services, you agree to be bound by these
          Terms of Service and all applicable laws and regulations. If you do
          not agree with any of these terms, you are prohibited from using or
          accessing our services.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">2. Services</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          {SITE_NAME} provides digital marketing services including but not limited
          to website design, social media management, pay-per-click advertising,
          SEO services, and indoor billboard advertising. The specific services provided
          will be outlined in individual service agreements.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">
          3. Payment Terms
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          Payment terms will be specified in your service agreement. Fees are
          typically due monthly or upon project completion unless otherwise
          specified. Late payments may result in service suspension or
          termination.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">
          4. Client Responsibilities
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Clients are responsible for:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 mb-6 space-y-2">
          <li>
            Providing accurate information and materials necessary for service
            delivery
          </li>
          <li>Timely review and approval of deliverables</li>
          <li>
            Maintaining active communication throughout the project or service
            period
          </li>
          <li>Ensuring they have rights to any materials provided to us</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">
          5. Intellectual Property
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          Upon full payment, clients own the final deliverables. We retain the
          right to showcase completed work in our portfolio unless otherwise
          agreed. Clients grant us license to use their brand materials solely
          for the purpose of providing the agreed-upon services.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">
          6. Service Modifications
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          We reserve the right to modify or discontinue services with reasonable
          notice to clients. Active service agreements will be honored through
          their term or transitioned appropriately.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">
          7. Limitation of Liability
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          {SITE_NAME} will not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential,
          or punitive damages resulting from your use of our services. Our total
          liability shall not exceed the amount paid for the specific service in
          question.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">
          8. Termination
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          Either party may terminate services with written notice as specified
          in the service agreement. Clients remain responsible for payment of
          services rendered prior to termination.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">
          9. Confidentiality
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          We respect the confidentiality of client information and will not
          disclose sensitive business information without permission, except as
          required by law.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">
          10. Governing Law
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          These terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the
          laws of the State of Texas, without regard to its conflict of law
          provisions.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">
          11. Changes to Terms
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Changes will
          be effective immediately upon posting to this page. Continued use of
          our services constitutes acceptance of modified terms.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">
          12. Contact Information
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          For questions about these Terms of Service, please contact us at <a
            href="/contact-us"
            class="text-primary hover:underline">our contact page</a
          >.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
